channel.description: IndyWarz Radio is the PREMIER LIVE internet radio show. We deal specifically with the top Independent Wrestling Promotions from around the WORLD. We have interviews EVERY show and allow your calls during the show. So, if you want to ask a question of a guest, you can just call in. We rarely, if ever, talk much about WWE or TNA. They have to much money invested in their weekly TV shows. They dont need my help. So, if you have news or anything about those two promotions, save it for another show. IndyWarz Radio also has some of the living legends on the show. We will have them on to talk about wrestling in the past as well as any independent dates they have coming up. So, Log In & Listen!

item.title: Ladies Night - Lillie Mae, Ms Dislexia & Kacee Carlisle - Jan 31,2012
item.description:
Lillie Mae, is a down to earth country girl. Who loves having a good time and being with good friends. She says shes happy go lucky and is always trying to better herself. She says if you would like to know anything else, just ask. So we will. We have a huge list of questions to ask, This is from Ms Dislexias FaceBook profile: I am open and honest. I am a big softee. I love what I do. School and work keep me pretty busy, but I still make time to have a life. I am hyper, I talk A lot.... I love being around friends and people that can make me laugh, and I hope I do the same for them. I am very random and pretty outspoken.... You just have to get to know me. So, we have some random questions to keep her entertained during the show. Kacee Carlisle will ba on as well. Now, this will make her 4th or 5th appearance on IndyWarz Radio. She has been a blast every time, so this should be no different.

item.title: C Diddy & David Fuller - Jan 17,2012
item.description:
C Diddy has been around for years here in Texas. Has traveled all over the U.S. with various promotions. He will have his final match on January 28 in Balch Springs, TX. We will have him on to talk about TX Stampede Wrestling and some of the stories from his travels up and down the road. IHWE Owner & At times Center of Controversy David Fuller sits down & addresses everything from his career, life as a promoter, his mistakes, his critics, heat, addiction, injuries & stories with some very notable wrestling talent. This will be uncensored & Fuller will hold nothing back. This is a cant miss for any fan of Texas!

item.title: Mike Foxx, Lance Hoyt & Tony Brooklyn - Jan 10,2012
item.description:
Tonight we have Mike Foxx, one of the staples at the PCW arena and around all of Texas. He has even been to WWE for dark matches and television. He is returning to the ring on Jan 28, 2012 for NWA Lonestars One More Time. Well get all the low down from Mike. Lance Hoyt has also been asked to come on. Besides his WWE and TNA appearances, he spends quite a bit of time in Japan. So, when hes available, we like to have him on the show. Tony Brooklyn will be on to talk NWA in Texas. I would have to say that Tony has spearheaded the movement to have NWA become a force in Texas. Lets see what Tony has to say. And never forget, Super Fan Jason will be on to read results as only Jason can.

item.title: Simply Luscious, Kacee Carlisle & Melissa Coates on IndyWarz Radio's Ladies Night! - Mar 22,2011
item.description:
Simply Luscious studied karate and ballet before getting into wrestling. She became the only female graduate of the Shawn Michaels' Texas Wrestling Academy, where she trained along with Paul London, Brian Kendrick, Matt Bentley and Bryan Danielson. She made her in-ring debut against Chris Marval in San Antonio, Texas, under the name "Simply Luscious", a moniker she got from her ex-husband, hockey player Ryan Pisiak. Soon after debuting, Luscious appeared briefly in World Championship Wrestling in a spot with Tank Abbott, where she received a concussion from Abbot. In 2003, Luscious was brought up to work for the Total Nonstop Action Wrestling promotion as a Knockout. She was given the new ring name "Nurse Veronica" and became the leader of an all-female group known as "Bitchslap" with Tracy and Valentina. However, the group was short-lived as Stevens turned down a two-year contract with TNA, instead attempting to sign with either World Wrestling Entertainment or a company in Japan. Kacee Carlisle is obnoxious, loud, annoying pain in the butt who loves to beat people up and run her mouth. She have no problem telling the fans, and her opponents, just what she think of them. But of course, she tries to be cute doing it! Melissa Coates trained at both Killer Kowalski's training school and Ultimate Pro Wrestling's Ultimate University, Coates then moved down to Louisville, Kentucky to begin training in World Wrestling Entertainment's developmental territory Ohio Valley Wrestling. Coates then made an appearance at WWE's Backlash, taking part in Chris Masters' "Masterlock Challenge" segment, where he offered $1000 to anyone who could break his Master Lock, which she failed to do. She was then placed in OVW as an official trainee and became the "head of security" for Kenny Bolin's stable "Bolin's Services". Soon after, however, Coates left both OVW and WWE and went to work for World Xtreme Wrestling. This is going to be a great show. LOG IN & LISTEN!

item.description:

Hell, he even had a deal with WWE for a short time. He will be on to talk about the difference between the Indy's here and the Indy's in Europe. We will also talk about his few trips he's made through Texas as well. I also have some emails out to some of the guys in this years Texas J-Cup, but they seem harder to get in touch with than the national guys. Go figure... The sow starts at 8PM CST.
